    "body": "`request` is rather heavy, a per your own notes on recent improvements to [`startup time`][startup-time].\r\n\r\nI looked through and it seems all of the usage is rather trivial: \r\n\r\n- [`/lib/doctor/get-latest-nodejs-version.js#L9`][get-latest-nodejs-version]\r\n- [`/lib/search/esearch.js#L35`][esearch]\r\n- [`/lib/owner.js#L254`][owner]\r\n\r\n`npm` doesn't event seem to be using it for JSON parsing, streaming or even handling redirects _(the most common & core functionality useful here that I can think of)_.\r\n\r\nam I missing some other parts where a mode deep usage of `request` is needed? otherwise, I can see a quick performance gain / over all improvement in using native `http.request`. would be more than happy to prototype, test and create PR.\r\n\r\n#### I'm opening this issue because:\r\n\r\n  - [x] Other (_see below for feature requests_):\r\n\r\n#### What's going wrong?\r\n\r\n- nothing broken\r\n- asking a question to get clarity on dependencies choice. \r\n- looking to help contribute.\r\n\r\n[startup-time]: https://github.com/npm/npm/blob/bc3f24bf95abe45a185848561c7c1edc90f60c5e/CHANGELOG.md#faster-startup-sometimes\r\n[get-latest-nodejs-version]: https://github.com/npm/npm/blob/d46015256941ddfff1463338e3e2f8f77624a1ff/lib/doctor/get-latest-nodejs-version.js#L9\r\n[esearch]: https://github.com/npm/npm/blob/d46015256941ddfff1463338e3e2f8f77624a1ff/lib/search/esearch.js#L35\r\n[owner]: https://github.com/npm/npm/blob/d46015256941ddfff1463338e3e2f8f77624a1ff/lib/owner.js#L254"
